Start the backend engine with hot-reload enabled:

```bash
npm run engine
```

The engine will start on `http://localhost:8000`.

### Running the Dashboard

In a separate terminal, start the frontend:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Visit `http://localhost:5173` (or the port shown in terminal) to access the Tadpole OS interface.

## üõ°Ô∏è Oversight & Safety

The **Oversight Gate** is the core safety mechanism.

1.  When an agent wants to execute a tool (e.g., `shell`, `fs`, [fetch](file:///C:/Users/Home%20Office_PC/.gemini/antigravity/brain/465cc492-80ff-4ba3-a4e3-5706db959613/Tadpole-OS/src/pages/OversightDashboard.tsx#55-77)), it pauses.
2.  The request appears in the **Oversight Dashboard**.
3.  You must manually click **"Approve"** for the action to proceed.
4.  If you **"Reject"**, the agent is notified and execution stops or retries.

## üß† Architecture

- **Gateway ([server/gateway.ts](file:///C:/Users/Home%20Office_PC/.gemini/antigravity/brain/465cc492-80ff-4ba3-a4e3-5706db959613/Tadpole-OS/server/gateway.ts)):** Express API + WebSocket server.
- **Runner ([server/runner.ts](file:///C:/Users/Home%20Office_PC/.gemini/antigravity/brain/465cc492-80ff-4ba3-a4e3-5706db959613/Tadpole-OS/server/runner.ts)):** The main loop that manages Agent <-> LLM interaction.
- **Skills (`server/skills/`):**
    - `shell`: Execute terminal commands.
    - `fs`: Read/Write files.
    - [fetch](file:///C:/Users/Home%20Office_PC/.gemini/antigravity/brain/465cc492-80ff-4ba3-a4e3-5706db959613/Tadpole-OS/src/pages/OversightDashboard.tsx#55-77): HTTP requests.
- **Provider ([server/providers/gemini.ts](file:///C:/Users/Home%20Office_PC/.gemini/antigravity/brain/465cc492-80ff-4ba3-a4e3-5706db959613/Tadpole-OS/server/providers/gemini.ts)):** Adapter for Google Generative AI.

## üß¨ Self-Evolution

The engine is designed to evolve. The agent has access to the `fs` skill and can be instructed to read `server/` files and propose edits.

> **Note:** API Rate Limits apply. Google Gemini Free Tier allows ~15 requests/minute. Heavy evolution tasks may hit this limit.

